"line2pdf" is a simple command-line utility to convert text into PDF.

    line2pdf [OPTIONS] [FILE]
      A simple program to convert lines of text into a PDF file.
    
    Common flags:
      -l --latin         Default encoding
      -b --big5    
      -g --gbk     
         --euc-jp  
         --euc-kr  
      -s --shiftjis
      -f --fontsize=INT  Font size in points (default 12)
      -? --help          Display help message
      -V --version       Print version information
    
    Convert a text file into PDF. The only formatting that is supported
    are new lines and page breaks, indicated by a Form Feed character (^L).
    The PDF is written to stdout.
    
    Examples:
      line2pdf in.txt > out.pdf
      line2pdf --shiftjis in.txt > out.pdf

